The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mangalore, Jan. 25 (PTI): Ten suspected activists of Sri Ram Sena have been taken into custody for assaulting revellers in a pub in the heart of Mangalore.           
	About 15 to 20 activists allegedly barged into the pub late last night and assaulted boys and girls there for dancing in an obscene manner, inspector general of police A.M. Prasad said.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): K.C. Verma, the internal security adviser to home minister P. Chidambaram, will be the next chief of countrys external intelligence agency RAW. Verma, a 1971-batch Jharkhand cadre officer, will take over from Ashok Chaturvedi on January 31, official said.                   
	 Porayar (PTI): An industrialist has presented a crown made of 500gm gold and 150 blue diamonds worth Rs 10 lakh to the Lord Saneeswara Temple at Tirunallar in Karaikal district of Tamil Nadu. Venkatesh Choudhary, owner of an airport and infrastructure company, had bagged a Rs 120-crore-contract.                  
	 Dehradun (PTI): The Uttarakhand government will open at least 100 centres to sell cow urine. The urine would be used to make medicines that will be sent to other states, animal husbandry and agricultural minister said Trivendra Rawat said.                   
	 Chennai (PTI): Four persons, including three children, were charred to death in Chennai when their hut caught fire on Sunday. Ashok Kumar, 35, a security guard, and his children were killed in the fire that could have been caused by sparks from a mosquito coil, police said.                   
	 Aligarh (PTI): Union minister Arjun Singh          
	 will inaugurate a two-day national seminar on minority education on January 31 at Aligarh Muslim University. The seminar aims to link the university with other minority educational institutions in the country, the vice-chancellor said.                                                                                                                           
